## 🧱 Architecture (four layers: CEO → Sub-agent SP → Skill → MCP/CLI)
- **Capability axis:** deterministic code (executed, never in context) ──documented──▶ Skill (`.claude/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`).
- **Role axis:** sub-agent (the worker) ──defined by──▶ its system prompt (`.claude/agents/<name>.md`); the SP holds pointers ("this role mainly uses skill X").
- **Rules:** ① freeze recurring mechanical steps into CLI subcommands (deterministic, zero-token); ② a reusable capability = a skill pointing at the root code; ③ the LLM decides, the CLI executes.
> **🔗 Propagation-consistency standing rule:** before any leaf change (CLI / skill / SP / template) is done, run a propagation analysis and confirm each upper layer's contract is still in sync. Machine backstop = `{{core}} doctor` (claims vs filesystem reality; non-zero on drift).

